## React Best Practices

### useEffect Dependency Management
- **Avoid infinite loops**: Be careful with dependency arrays to prevent infinite re-renders
- **Specific object properties**: Use `session?.session_token` instead of `session` in dependencies
- **Avoid circular dependencies**: Don't include functions that depend on state updated inside the same effect
- **Move logic inside effect**: When a function creates circular dependencies, move the logic inside the effect as a local function

#### Common Patterns:
```javascript
// ✅ GOOD: Use specific property
useEffect(() => {
  if (session?.session_token) {
    fetchData(session.session_token);
  }
}, [session?.session_token]); // Only re-run when token changes

// ❌ BAD: Using entire object
useEffect(() => {
  if (session?.session_token) {
    fetchData(session.session_token);
  }
}, [session]); // Re-runs whenever any session property changes

// ✅ GOOD: Move dependent logic inside effect
useEffect(() => {
  const getCurrentUserId = () => {
    // Logic that depends on state
    return users.find(u => u.id === tokenUserId)?.id;
  };

  const userId = getCurrentUserId();
  // Use userId...
}, [sessionToken, users]); // Only essential dependencies

// ❌ BAD: Function in dependencies that depends on updated state
useEffect(() => {
  const userId = getCurrentUserId();
  // Use userId...
}, [getCurrentUserId]); // Circular dependency if getCurrentUserId depends on state updated here
```

